messages.message:
I’m adding these back in the update today @avi, but I had to fuss with the release question to get a satisfactory answer. As way of feedback, I tried the following:
• _What are the new features in the latest AI Hub release?_ This gave me a long list of features from various releases.
• _What is the latest release of AI Hub, and what features are in it?_ This gave me a list of features from 23.43(?!?)
• _What is the the most recent release of AI Hub, and what features are in it?_ This was the winner and gave me a correct answer.

I added back the release question, the model question, and the Python code question. Then I ran out of credits :joy:  I will add the last question later, but I’m traveling to SF today, so it will have to be later and only if I have credits.

Awesome, thanks @jean :raised_hands::skin-tone-4:
1. It's useful to have this feedback about the prompt iteration. Ideally we beef up the model to support these out of box. @Hari @vineeth @Sławek Biel FYI
2. For the credits issue, I pinged in https://instabase.slack.com/archives/C05BJCNKZAM/p1720669981194339 to try to get the service account loaded with more credits 
Let me know once you update the docsbot with these sample prompts, I can make sure to republish the latest version to the marketplace
